## Version System & Page ID Requirements

### MANDATORY: Page ID System Implementation
**EVERY page/screen/component MUST include PageIdDisplay for development tracking and AI assistance.**

#### Page ID Format & Assignment
All pages use hierarchical IDs with format: `[Category][Number]`

**Categories:**
- **T**: Tab pages (T1, T2, T3, etc.)
- **A**: Auth pages (A1, A2, A3, etc.)  
- **M**: Modal pages (M1, M2, M3, etc.)
- **R**: Root pages (R1, R2, R3, etc.)

**Current Page ID Assignments:**
```typescript
// Tab Pages (T)
T0: Tabs Layout, T1: Today, T2: Week, T3: Month, T4: Add Event, 
T5: Food Trucks, T6: Search, T7: Admin

// Auth Pages (A)  
A0: Auth Layout, A1: Auth Index, A2: Login, A3: Forgot Password,
A4: Reset Password, A5: Accept Invite, A6: Auth Redirect

// Modal Pages (M)
M1: Create Account, M2: Create Food Truck Contact, M3: Create Food Truck Event,
M4: Data Management, M5: Edit Enums, M6: Event Detail, M7: Food Order Report,
M8: Food Truck All Events, M9: Food Truck Detail, M10: Import Summary, M11: Manage Users

// Root Pages (R)
R1: Root Index, R2: Root Layout, R3: Invite Redirect
```

#### Implementation Requirements for ALL Pages

**1. Required Imports:**
```typescript
// Components
import { PageIdDisplay } from '../../src/components/common/PageIdDisplay';

// Version system
import { PAGE_IDS } from '../../src/constants/version';
```

**2. Component Placement:**
```typescript
export default function YourPageScreen(): React.JSX.Element {
  // ... component logic ...

  return (
    <View style={[styles.container, dynamicStyles.container]}>
      <PageIdDisplay pageId={PAGE_IDS.YOUR_PAGE_ID} />
      {/* Rest of your component */}
    </View>
  );
}
```

**3. Multiple Return Statements:**
For pages with loading states, error states, or authorization checks, add PageIdDisplay to ALL return statements:

```typescript
// Loading state
if (loading) {
  return (
    <View style={styles.container}>
      <PageIdDisplay pageId={PAGE_IDS.YOUR_PAGE_ID} />
      <ActivityIndicator />
    </View>
  );
}

// Error state  
if (error) {
  return (
    <View style={styles.container}>
      <PageIdDisplay pageId={PAGE_IDS.YOUR_PAGE_ID} />
      {renderErrorState()}
    </View>
  );
}

// Main render
return (
  <View style={styles.container}>
    <PageIdDisplay pageId={PAGE_IDS.YOUR_PAGE_ID} />
    {/* Main content */}
  </View>
);
```

